                    "description": "Research: Laboratory based research of the inter- and circumstellar medium / Special focus on (high resolution) molecular gas phase transients / Characterisation of physical and chemical processes in interstellar ice analogues (desorption, dissociation, chemistry) / Photofragmentation of PAHs / Astronomical observations and astrochemical modelling.\n\nTeaching: Lecturer (currently: 1st year course 'Introduction to Astronomy') / Supervisor Bachelor and Master research projects / Chairman Educational Committee Astronomy.\n\nScience policy: Board member of the European Task Force for Laboratory Astrophysics / Research coordinator FP7 ITN LASSIE / Coordinator Solid State research within Dutch Astrochemistry Program / Coordinator 'Biosignatures' within Dutch Exoplanetary Call / Editor 'Comment on Atomic and Molecular Physics' / Chairman IAU297 / SOC FD168 / SOC Symposium on IR plasma spectroscopy.\n\nOutreach: Public lectures (for 6 to 90+ yrs) / Youth University / Column 'Hemel boven Vreeland' / Popular scientific articles.\n\nSee www.laboratory-astrophysics.eu",
